      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "---> Dividing categorical features and continuous features"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "EK1FdQn_jbg-"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "categorical = ['sex', 'cp', 'fbs', 'restecg', 'exang', 'slope', 'thal', 'ca']\n",
        "continuous = ['age', 'trestbps', 'chol', 'thalach', 'oldpeak']"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "-spt_9i7Htt_"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "--> One-Hot encoding for the categorical features"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "GWXre1uljlkx"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "def preprocess(heart):\n",
        "    heart = heart.copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 1. Heart rate achievement ratio\n",
        "    heart['hr_ratio'] = heart['thalach'] / (220 - heart['age'] + 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 2. ST depression severity flags\n",
        "    heart['st_depression_high'] = (heart['oldpeak'] > 2).astype(int)\n",
        "    heart['st_depression_mild'] = (\n",
        "        (heart['oldpeak'] > 1) & (heart['oldpeak'] <= 2)\n",
        "    ).astype(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 3. Exercise combined risk\n",
        "    heart['exercise_risk'] = heart['exang'] * heart['oldpeak']\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 4. Vessel + ST depression severity\n",
        "    heart['severity_score'] = heart['ca'] + heart['oldpeak']\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 5. Age risk band (ordinal encoded)\n",
        "    heart['age_risk_band'] = pd.cut(\n",
        "        heart['age'],\n",
        "        bins=[0, 45, 55, 65, 120],\n",
        "        labels=[0, 1, 2, 3]\n",
        "    ).astype(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "    heart['age_thalach'] = heart['age'] * heart['thalach']\n",
        "    heart['chol_age'] = heart['chol'] / (heart['age'] + 1)\n",
        "    heart['age_chol_ratio'] = heart['age'] / (heart['chol'] + 1)\n",
        "    heart['oldpeak_slope'] = heart['oldpeak'] * heart['slope']\n",
        "\n",
        "    heart['high_risk_profile'] = (\n",
        "        ((heart['cp'] == 1) | (heart['cp'] == 2)) &\n",
        "        ((heart['thal'] == 1) | (heart['thal'] == 2))\n",
        "    ).astype(int)\n",
        "    return heart\n",
        "class Preprocess(BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin):\n",
        "    def fit(self, X, y=None):\n",
        "        X_transformed = self._transform(X)\n",
        "        self.feature_names_ = X_transformed.columns.tolist()  # added - remembers train columns\n",
        "        return self\n",
        "\n",
        "    def transform(self, X):\n",
        "        X_transformed = self._transform(X)\n",
        "        return X_transformed.reindex(columns=self.feature_names_, fill_value=0)  # added - aligns test to train\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _transform(self, X):         # added - extracted helper\n",
        "        X = preprocess(X.copy())\n",
        "        return pd.get_dummies(X, drop_first=True)   # added - encoding now lives here"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "97ofa9wrqM3m"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.model_selection import RandomizedSearchCV\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import OneHotEncoder\n",
        "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
        "# Parameters of RandomForest\n",
        "pipe_rf = Pipeline([\n",
        "    ('preprocess', Preprocess()),\n",
        "    ('model', RandomForestClassifier(random_state=42))\n",
        "])\n",
        "param_rf = {\n",
        "    'model__n_estimators': [200,250, 300,350,400, 500],\n",
        "    'model__max_depth': [None, 4,5,6,7,8, 9],\n",
        "    'model__min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10],\n",
        "    'model__min_samples_leaf': [1, 2, 4],\n",
        "    'model__max_features': ['sqrt', 'log2']\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "rf_search = RandomizedSearchCV(\n",
        "    pipe_rf, param_rf,\n",
        "    n_iter=50, cv=5,\n",
        "    scoring='f1',\n",
        "    n_jobs=-1,\n",
        "    random_state=42\n",
        ")\n",
        "rf_search.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Assigning the best parameters\n",
        "rf = rf_search.best_estimator_\n",
        "print(\"Best params for Random Forest\", rf_search.best_params_)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Defining the pipeline for Logistic Regression\n",
        "pipe_lg = Pipeline([\n",
        "    ('preprocess', Preprocess()),\n",
        "    ('scaler', StandardScaler()),\n",
        "    ('model', LogisticRegression(random_state=42))\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Parameters of Logistic Regression\n",
        "param_lg = [\n",
        "    {\n",
        "        'model__solver': ['liblinear'],\n",
        "        'model__penalty': ['l1', 'l2'],\n",
        "        'model__C': np.logspace(-3, 3, 10)\n",
        "    },\n",
        "    {\n",
        "        'model__solver': ['saga'],\n",
        "        'model__penalty': ['l1', 'l2', 'elasticnet'],\n",
        "        'model__C': np.logspace(-3, 3, 10),\n",
        "        'model__l1_ratio': [0.2, 0.5, 0.8]\n",
        "    }\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "log_search = RandomizedSearchCV(\n",

        "\n",
        "# Assigning the best parameters\n",
        "lg = log_search.best_estimator_\n",
        "print(\"Best Logistic params:\", log_search.best_params_)"
      ],

      "source": [
        "### Threshold Tuning & Model Evaluation after Threshold Tuning"
      ],

        "id": "rVXD2esBly54"

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.metrics import precision_recall_curve\n",
        "\n",
        "best=[]\n",
        "for name, model in models.items():\n",
        "    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)\n",
        "    y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]\n",
        "    precision, recall, thresholds = precision_recall_curve(y_test, y_prob)\n",
        "\n",
        "    target_recall = 0.90\n",
        "    valid_idx = np.where(recall[:-1] >= target_recall)[0]\n",
        "    if len(valid_idx) == 0:\n",
        "        print(f\"Warning: {name} cannot achieve recall >= {target_recall}. Using lowest threshold.\")\n",
        "        best_threshold = thresholds[0]\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        best_threshold = thresholds[valid_idx[-1]]  # highest threshold still achieving target recall\n",
        "\n",
        "    print('=====================================================')\n",
        "    print(f'{name} at {best_threshold:.3f} threshold')\n",
        "    print('=====================================================')\n",
        "    y_pred_tuned = (y_prob >= best_threshold).astype(int)\n",
        "    print('Accuracy:', accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_tuned))\n",
        "    print('ROC_AUC:', roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob))\n",
        "    print(confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_tuned))\n",
        "    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred_tuned),\"\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    best.append({'Model': name, 'Best Threshold': best_threshold, 'F1 Score': f1_score(y_test, y_pred_tuned)})\n",
        "best_df = pd.DataFrame(best).sort_values(by='F1 Score', ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "print('=======================================================')\n",
        "print(best_df)"
